title: For Sale:  AUTO-ORDANCE 1911 THOMPSON .45 ACP SEMI-AUTO
postcontent:
SOLD

This is an Auto-Ordnance “Thompson” line of 1911 style pistols. Thompson pistols are still being made under their current owner Kahr Arms. This particular one pre-dates that acquisition and is sometimes called a “West Hurley” Thompson, named after the manufacture city of its time.

In its early years of production it was made from military parts on a Essex frame and slide with a commercial colt barrel. The highest quality guns are thought to be SN AOC4000 and lower. (This gun is AOC22**) It's manufacture date is pre-1983. At a weighty 46.7 oz (2 lbs, 14.7oz), this Thompson is a hefty, dark, sleek looking gun. The front sight is a massive blade with no angle cuts to it.  Hogue wrap-around combat grips were added and provide an excellent grip for shooting. It has a beautiful patina, with some wear typical of a shooter of it's age. Included is a Pachmayer 7 rd. magazine.

This is a great  1911 .45ACP shooter!
